commit.message:
Test data for lsraid

The lsraid plugin is marked broken because of missing test data. This commit adds lsraid output for centos2 and centos3 hosts.
The plugin is seemingly broken though because it expects a single space instead of multiple spaces inside the regex. It also will ignore missing disks as they do not match the regex.

Parse 3ware VERIFY-PAUSED as okay

The 3ware controllers can show a a logical unit as `VERIFY-PAUSED` in case the controller has multiple units and they are being verified serially.

Do not consider this a CRITICAL error but instead parse it as a regular VERIFY state.

```

Unit  UnitType  Status         %RCmpl  %V/I/M  Stripe  Size(GB)  Cache  AVrfy
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
u0    RAID-10   VERIFYING      -       4%      64K     1490.06   W      ON
u1    SPARE     VERIFY-PAUSED  -       0%      -       298.082   -      ON
u2    SPARE     VERIFY-PAUSED  -       0%      -       298.082   -      ON
```

commit.message:
arcconf.pm: Parse 'Reported Location' when devices are directly attached

Some devices are reported for instance as

Reported Location                    : Enclosure Direct Attached, Slot 0(Connector 0:CN0)

Include those variants in the parsing for the location of a device. This
will result in the identification for the enclosure to be tracked as
'Direct Attached'.

Signed-off-by: Salvatore Bonaccorso <carnil@debian.org>

arcconf.pm: For now skip some new sections

Skip 'Array Information', 'Array Physical Device Information' and
'maxCache information' sections for parsing.

Add empty subs accordingly for later expansion and retaining a TODO
item.

Signed-off-by: Salvatore Bonaccorso <carnil@debian.org>

arcconf.pm: Skip lines in subsections which consinst of empty lines

Some subjections are of the form

   --------------------------------------------------------
   Connector information

   --------------------------------------------------------

so we need to track as well potential empty lines (with spaces inbetween
the section markers to track.

Signed-off-by: Salvatore Bonaccorso <carnil@debian.org>

t/check_arcconf.t: Add new test cases for improved arcconf parsing

Signed-off-by: Salvatore Bonaccorso <carnil@debian.org>

commit.message: Add test info for pull request #207
hpacucli plugin fix case with missing controllers

cciss: add test for cciss_vol_status 1.12(a) output

This adds a test case which contains all changes to cciss_vol_status
1.12 and 1.12a output.

cciss: adapt for new cache information

Since v1.12, cciss_vol_status outputs these two new extra lines about
cache status:

        Total cache memory: 816 MiB
               Cache Ratio: 10% Read / 90% Write

Make sure we parse them and include them in cstatus, so that they also
end up in the test dump files which makes the tests pass again.

cciss: adapt for changed physical drive output

In version 1.12a, cciss_vol_status changes the output of physical location of drives:

    -       sprintf(tail, " connector %c%c box %d bay %d %40s %40s %8s",
    +       sprintf(tail, " connector %c%c box %d bay %-2d %40s %40s %8s",

This means that the bay number is now 2 posititions, left aligned.
So, e.g. '1 ', '6 ', or '12'.

Allow for an extra space to be present when the bay number is less than
10.

Without this change, the pattern will not match any more, and the
program complains about Unparsed lines.
